tsburgh business times enlarge pittmoss founder mont handley got  in funding from the investors in abcs shark… more filejustine coyne a pittsburgh startup that counts three shark tank panelists including mt lebanon native mark cuban among its investors has parted ways with its founder and top officer mont handley who founded pittmoss llc and created its namesake product a peat moss substitute made from a mix of organic additives and recycled paper is no longer president and ceo confirmed michael matesic an independent director of the ambridgebased company enlarge pittmoss founder mont handley got  in funding from the investors in abcs shark… more filejustine coyne “we are talking with an interim ceo who could be brought on as soon as next week” said matesic who is ceo of idea foundry an original investor in pittmoss “the company is actively working to identify a replacement ceo” matesic declined comment about handley and the circumstances of the change a call to handley was not returned handley had experimented with the food processor his mother gave him when he graduated from purdue university to develop a sustainable alternative to peat moss working on the project off and on for a couple of decades pittmoss technically launched in  but two years later handley quit his job as national sales director at visionpittsburgh to focus on his startup full time in april  handley appeared on the abctv reality show “shark tank” to pitch its wealthy entrepreneur panelists to invest in pittmoss selling them on the potential of the product which is used in soil mixtures demonstrating superior growing outcomes while lowering costs atypically for the show three — cuban kevin o’leary and robert herjavec — came in together the sharks jointly contributed  in a funding round where pittmoss raised  million the other investors were local — bluetree allied angels idea foundry angels with attitude and innovation works patty tascarella covers banking finance and the legal industry contact 